---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About MaiPDF | Online Cloud Sharing and App DRM"
  description="MaiPDF builds secure PDF sharing in two clear paths: Online Cloud Sharing for browser links and App DRM for protected .maipdf files in the MaiPDF Secure App."
  lang="en"
>
  <main class="about-secure">
    <section class="about-hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">MaiPDF Secure</p>
      <h1>Two practical paths for secure PDF sharing</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        MaiPDF helps people share PDFs with the right level of control. Use Online Cloud Sharing when readers need a fast browser link or QR code. Use App DRM when a document needs a protected reader, device rules, revocation, and stronger screenshot-aware controls.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn primary" href="/blog/en/online-pdf-sharing-vs-app-drm">Read the product overview</a>
        <a class="btn secondary" href="https://drm.maipdf.com">Explore App DRM</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="split-paths" aria-label="MaiPDF product paths">
      <article class="path-card online">
        <span class="path-label">maipdf.com</span>
        <h2>Online Cloud Sharing</h2>
        <p>
          The fast path for PDF links, QR codes, browser reading, expiry, view limits, dynamic watermarks, access records, and online file replacement.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Best for quick sharing and no-install readers</li>
          <li>Works well for proposals, portfolios, reports, and class handouts</li>
          <li>Controls the online link, not a local protected file</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="https://maipdf.com">Start online sharing →</a>
      </article>

      <article class="path-card appdrm">
        <span class="path-label">drm.maipdf.com</span>
        <h2>App DRM / .maipdf</h2>
        <p>
          The stronger path for valuable documents that should open inside the MaiPDF Secure App instead of an ordinary browser or generic PDF reader.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Protected .maipdf files and license checks</li>
          <li>Device binding, recipient control, expiry, and revocation</li>
          <li>Stronger screen-capture controls where the platform supports them</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="https://drm.maipdf.com">Open App DRM →</a>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Direction</p>
        <h2>MaiPDF is moving toward a clearer Secure App identity</h2>
      </div>
      <p>
        Older MaiPDF pages and diagrams sometimes used purple-blue gradients, rounded SaaS cards, many small buttons, red arrows, and legacy flowcharts. That style no longer represents the main product direction. New pages should feel closer to a professional DRM product: white and light-gray surfaces, deep blue emphasis, green success states, and clear security status messaging.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section grid-3">
      <article>
        <h3>Honest browser limits</h3>
        <p>Browser links can add useful controls, but they cannot fully control the operating system or guarantee screenshot blocking.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Stronger app control</h3>
        <p>App DRM changes the risk model by requiring the protected file to open through the MaiPDF Secure App and a valid license.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Traceable sharing</h3>
        <p>Watermarks, access records, open limits, and expiry remain important because no software can stop every possible copy method.</p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section legacy-note">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Legacy content</p>
        <h2>Older HTML / Offline DRM material is now secondary</h2>
      </div>
      <p>
        MaiPDF may still keep older HTML-package or Offline DRM references for existing users and historical documentation. They should not be the main message for new readers. The current recommendation is simple: Online Cloud Sharing for fast browser delivery, App DRM / .maipdf for stronger protected-reader workflows.
      </p>
      <a href="/blog/en/online-pdf-sharing-vs-app-drm">Compare Online Cloud Sharing and App DRM →</a>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section grid-2">
      <article>
        <p class="eyebrow">Built since 2019</p>
        <h2>Practical document control</h2>
        <p>
          MaiPDF has been developed as a practical tool for controlled PDF distribution: links, QR codes, watermarks, reading records, access limits, and stronger protected-file workflows when the document is sensitive.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <p class="eyebrow">Related tools</p>
        <h2>Privacy-focused products</h2>
        <p>
          In addition to MaiPDF, we also operate privacy and sharing tools such as privnote.chat. The common goal is simple: help people share information with more control than ordinary attachments and public links.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section resources">
      <p class="eyebrow">Recommended reading</p>
      <h2>Start with the current product explanation</h2>
      <div class="resource-links">
        <a href="/blog/en/online-pdf-sharing-vs-app-drm">Online PDF Sharing vs App DRM</a>
        <a href="/blog/en/what-is-a-maipdf-file">What is a .maipdf file?</a>
        <a href="/blog/en/secure-pdf-reader-with-screenshot-protection">Secure PDF reader with screenshot protection</a>
        <a href="/blog/en/how-to-open-a-maipdf-file">How to open a .maipdf file</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
<style>
.about-secure {
  max-width: 1120px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 56px 20px 88px;
  color: #0f172a;
  font-family: Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
}
.about-hero {
  border: 1px solid #dbe4ef;
  border-radius: 28px;
  padding: clamp(32px, 6vw, 72px);
  background:
    radial-gradient(circle at 90% 10%, rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.14), transparent 32%),
    linear-gradient(135deg, #ffffff 0%, #f8fafc 54%, #eef5ff 100%);
  box-shadow: 0 24px 70px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.08);
}
.eyebrow {
  margin: 0 0 12px;
  color: #1d4ed8;
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  font-weight: 800;
  letter-spacing: 0.14em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
}
.about-hero h1 {
  max-width: 820px;
  margin: 0;
  font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 7vw, 5.4rem);
  line-height: 0.95;
  letter-spacing: -0.055em;
}
.lead {
  max-width: 760px;
  margin: 26px 0 0;
  color: #334155;
  font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2vw, 1.3rem);
  line-height: 1.75;
}
.hero-actions {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 14px;
  margin-top: 32px;
}
.btn {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  min-height: 48px;
  padding: 0 20px;
  border-radius: 999px;
  font-weight: 800;
  text-decoration: none;
}
.btn.primary { background: #0f2f5f; color: #fff; }
.btn.secondary { background: #e8f1ff; color: #0f2f5f; border: 1px solid #c7d7ef; }
.split-paths {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  gap: 22px;
  margin: 28px 0;
}
.path-card, .about-section {
  border: 1px solid #dbe4ef;
  border-radius: 24px;
  background: #fff;
  box-shadow: 0 14px 45px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.06);
}
.path-card {
  padding: 30px;
}
.path-card h2, .about-section h2, .about-section h3 { color: #0f172a; }
.path-card h2 { margin: 10px 0 12px; font-size: 1.65rem; }
.path-card p, .path-card li, .about-section p { color: #475569; line-height: 1.7; }
.path-card ul { padding-left: 1.2rem; }
.path-card a, .legacy-note a, .resource-links a { color: #1d4ed8; font-weight: 800; text-decoration: none; }
.path-label {
  display: inline-flex;
  padding: 7px 11px;
  border-radius: 999px;
  font-size: 0.76rem;
  font-weight: 900;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
}
.online .path-label { background: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8; }
.appdrm .path-label { background: #ecfdf5; color: #047857; }
.appdrm { border-top: 5px solid #047857; }
.online { border-top: 5px solid #1d4ed8; }
.about-section {
  padding: 32px;
  margin-top: 24px;
}
.grid-3, .grid-2 {
  display: grid;
  gap: 18px;
}
.grid-3 { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr)); }
.grid-2 { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr)); }
.grid-3 article, .grid-2 article {
  padding: 22px;
  border-radius: 18px;
  background: #f8fafc;
  border: 1px solid #e7edf5;
}
.legacy-note {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fff 0%, #fff7ed 100%);
  border-color: #fed7aa;
}
.resources {
  background: #f8fafc;
}
.resource-links {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  gap: 12px;
  margin-top: 18px;
}
.resource-links a {
  padding: 16px 18px;
  border: 1px solid #dbe4ef;
  border-radius: 16px;
  background: #fff;
}
@media (max-width: 800px) {
  .split-paths, .grid-3, .grid-2, .resource-links { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .about-secure { padding-top: 28px; }
}
</style>

</Layout>
